  &lt;a data-nid=&quot;5966&quot; href=&quot;{{linkUrl}}&quot; ng-click=&quot;click($event)&quot;&gt;
    &lt;img nopin=&quot;nopin&quot; class=&quot;no-pin article-img&quot; ng-src=&quot;{{imgUrl}}&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;description-wrapper&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;article-title&quot;&gt;{{displayTitle}}&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;more&quot;&gt;
          &lt;span class=&quot;read-more&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;READ&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;i class=&quot;fa fa-long-arrow-right&quot;&gt;
      &lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Sriracha (pronounced sir-rotch-ah or sear-raw-chah) is a bright red hot sauce that&rsquo;s getting &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nytimes.com/2009/05/20/dining/20united.html?_r=0&quot; rel=&quot;&quot;&gt;seriously popular.&lt;/a&gt; The paste-like sauce&mdash;named after Sri Racha, Thailand&mdash;is made from chili peppers, vinegar, garlic, sugar, and salt. The versatile hot stuff provides low-cal flavor and can be used as a dipping sauce for just about anything, and is gaining fame as a go-to street-food condiment. If you want to sound extra cool, call it by its alias, &ldquo;rooster sauce.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;To get started, make your own sriracha with one of these recipes&mdash;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bluekaleroad.com/2013/01/homemade-sriracha.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;honeyed sriracha&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thegingercook.com/2010/09/homemade-sriracha-sauce.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;simple sriracha&lt;/a&gt;&mdash;or find it in most major grocery stores (typically in the Asian foods section) with a bright green cap and a rooster on the label. Added bonus: Besides firing up a meal, studies suggest the &lt;a href=&quot;http://npic.orst.edu/factsheets/Capgen.pdf&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;capsaicin&lt;/a&gt; in chili peppers can &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/cayenne-pepper-benefits/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;speed up metabolism&lt;/a&gt; and suppress appetite &lt;cite data-cite-reference=&quot;&quot; class=&quot;citation-reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19345452&quot; rel=&quot;&quot;&gt;Effects of capsaicin, green tea and CH-19 sweet pepper on appetite and energy intake in humans in negative and positive energy balance&lt;/a&gt;. Reinbach, HC., Smeets, A., Martinussen, T., et al. Department of Food Science, University of Copenhagen, Rolighedsvej 30, Frederiksberg C, Denmark. Clinical Nutrition (Edinburgh, Scotland), Jun; 28(3):260-5.&lt;/cite&gt; &lt;cite data-cite-reference=&quot;&quot; class=&quot;citation-reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21093467&quot; rel=&quot;&quot;&gt;The effects of hedonically acceptable red pepper doses on thermogenesis and appetite&lt;/a&gt;. Ludy, MJ, Mattes, RD. Purdue University, West Lafayette, Indiana. Physiology and Behavior, 2011 Mar 1;102(3-4):251-8.&lt;/cite&gt;. We&rsquo;ve rounded up some of our favorite healthier sriracha recipes, from &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/healthy-breakfast-snacks/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;healthy breakfast burritos&lt;/a&gt;, soups, and stews, to cocktails and sweet treats. Have a glass of water on the ready, because it&rsquo;s about to get hot up in here.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Breakfast&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;span   class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_full_width_inline_image&quot;   &gt;     &lt;img     src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/California%20Eggs%20Benedict%202.jpg?itok=Yb5yfob5&quot;            alt=&quot;California Eggs Benedict&quot;              class=&quot;media-element file-g-full-width-inline-image&quot;   /&gt;       &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;1. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thecurvycarrot.com/2012/03/26/california-eggs-benedict/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;California Eggs Benedict&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Add slices of avocado and tomato to fluffy poached eggs for a new take on the old classic. Make a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.eatingwell.com/recipes/hollandaise_sauce.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;healthier hollandaise&lt;/a&gt; (it&rsquo;s still creamy, but has a little less butter) with sriracha mixed right in.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;2. &lt;a href=&quot;http://natalieparamore.com/sweet-potato-breakfast-skillet-hash/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sweet Potato Breakfast Skillet Hash&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Counter the sweetness of sweet potatoes with sriracha, garlic, and an egg. Added Bonus: You just need one pan!&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;3. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zestuous.com/2012/08/quick-adobo-fried-rice-omelets/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Adobo Fried Rice Omelets&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These omelets don&rsquo;t rely on stereotypical fillings like cheese and veggies. Instead, they&rsquo;re stuffed with rice and &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/healthy-exciting-chicken-breast-recipes&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;chicken&lt;/a&gt; seasoned with ginger and soy sauce. For a healthier version, choose brown rice and low-sodium soy sauce.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;4. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bashfulbao.com/2012/11/sriracha-swirled-cornbread-muffins/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Swirled Cornbread Muffins&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These moist corn muffins have sriracha swirled right into the batter. Pack them for breakfasts on-the-go or top with cottage cheese or plain Greek yogurt for a &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/top-trainers-share-their-favorite-workout-snacks&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;protein-packed snack&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;5. &lt;a href=&quot;http://domesticfits.com/2012/05/14/jalapeno-corn-waffles-sriracha-maple-syrup-how-to-survive-online-bullies/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Jalape&ntilde;o Corn Waffles With Sriracha Maple Syrup&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This combination could not be more terrifying or enticing all at the same time. Cut back on some of the cheese and sub in whole-wheat flour for a &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/recipes/gluten-free-pumpkin-cheesecake-waffles&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;healthier waffle&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;6. &lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.thesrirachacookbook.com/post/36525790552/savory-sriracha-oatmeal-recipe&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Savory Oatmeal&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Ditch the fruit and other &ldquo;normal&rdquo; oatmeal fixings for sriracha, garlic, rosemary, and cashews. Top the dish with a sunny-side up &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/eggs/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;egg&lt;/a&gt; for extra protein, vitamins, and minerals.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;7. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bakeyourday.net/sriracha-veggie-frittata/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha and Veggie Frittata&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This frittata has tons of veggies and greens&mdash;spinach, red onion, peppers, mushrooms, and parsley&mdash;plus a mix of Parmesan and goat cheese. Sriracha goes right into the scramble, but a little drizzle on top is highly suggested.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Lunch&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;span   class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_full_width_inline_image&quot;   &gt;     &lt;img     src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/Summer%20Chopped%20Soba%20Noodle%20Salad.jpg?itok=13ScfSS0&quot;            alt=&quot;Summer Chopped Soba Noodle Salad&quot;              class=&quot;media-element file-g-full-width-inline-image&quot;   /&gt;       &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;8. &lt;a href=&quot;http://dailywaffle.com/2012/07/11/summer-chopped-vegetable-salad-w-soba/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Chopped Salad With Soba Noodles&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This clean eat has all sorts of healthy ingredients, including veggies, edamame, and cashews. Soba noodles are made from buckwheat&mdash;a &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/27-gluten-free-recipe-substitutions&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;gluten-free flour&lt;/a&gt;&mdash;but check the label anyway since some manufacturers sneak wheat in there!&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;9. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.inspiredtaste.net/12679/blt-summer-rolls-recipe/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;BLT Summer Rolls&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This recipe is quick, simple, and light. Stuff the rolls with small strips of bacon, lettuce, and tomato. The sriracha comes into play in the spicy-lime mayo. Find rice paper rolls in the international section of grocery stores or at Asian markets.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;10. &lt;a href=&quot;http://leafandgrain.com/sriracha-quinoa-bites/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Quinoa Bites&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These little &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/quinoa/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;quinoa&lt;/a&gt; bites can be made in a mini muffin pan or in a standard muffin pan for larger portions. The creamy Gruyere and honey help &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/best-way-to-soothe-burning-mouth&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;cool down the sriracha&rsquo;s heat&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;11. &lt;a href=&quot;http://rasamalaysia.com/lemongrass-grilled-shrimp/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Lemongrass Sriracha Grilled Shrimp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This Vietnamese-style dish takes less than 30 minutes to make and uses a garlic-lemongrass sriracha marinade. (Yum!) For extra heat, go buck wild with the chili dipping sauce. The &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/recipes/grilled-chicken-kabobs&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;skewers&lt;/a&gt; make for a pretty presentation for an appetizer or lunch.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;12. &lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.naturebox.com/post/35671352425/shrimp-quinoa-spring-rolls&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Shrimp Quinoa Spring Rolls&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Quinoa strikes again! This time it&rsquo;s used as a stand-in for rice in these &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/recipes/vegetable-spring-rolls-sweet-tahini-soy-sauce&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;healthier spring rolls&lt;/a&gt;. Julienned cucumbers and carrots accompany shrimp, lettuce, and quinoa inside rice paper wrappers. Dip them in a sriracha-infused peanut sauce to up the nom-factor.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;13. &lt;a href=&quot;http://appetiteforchina.com/recipes/sriracha-fried-rice/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Fried Rice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Choose brown rice and olive oil to make this spicy rice a slightly &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/35-quick-and-healthy-low-calorie-lunches&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;healthier lunch choice&lt;/a&gt;. Add some green with broccoli florets or bok choy, and beef up the meal with a protein like tofu, chicken, or steak.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;14. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kalynskitchen.com/2012/10/spicy-sriracha-tofu-peanut-butter.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spicy Peanut Butter Tofu&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Tofu isn&rsquo;t the most glamorous looking (or tasting) food. However, dousing it in garlic, ginger, soy sauce, sriracha, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/healthy-alternatives-peanut-butter&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;peanut butter&lt;/a&gt; make it much more appealing. The tofu slices are browned, and the sauce thickens when cooked for non-rubbery tofu that&rsquo;s anything but bland.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;15. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.closetcooking.com/2012/07/spicy-peanut-chicken-grilled-cheese.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Peanut Chicken Grilled Cheese&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Make the &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/ultimate-grilled-cheese/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;grilled cheese&lt;/a&gt; part of this recipe healthier by using whole-wheat toast, plain shredded chicken, and 1/4 cup of cheese. Believe us, there&rsquo;s still plenty of creaminess thanks to the peanut sauce and avocado, plus tons of flavor from cilantro and, of course, sriracha.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;16. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.tasteofhealthygoodness.com/2012/01/a-little-crunch-to-top-it-off/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Croutons&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Spice up a boring salad or &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/soups-and-stews&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;soup&lt;/a&gt; with hot croutons. This simple recipe calls for only four ingredients&mdash;bread, oil, sriracha, and garlic. Use whole-grain bread for a heartier bite.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Dinner&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;span   class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_full_width_inline_image&quot;   &gt;     &lt;img     src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/Black%20Bean%20Burger%20With%20Sriracha%20Sauce.jpg?itok=BFER3Pj_&quot;            alt=&quot;Black Bean Burger With Sriracha Sauce&quot;              class=&quot;media-element file-g-full-width-inline-image&quot;   /&gt;       &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;17. &lt;a href=&quot;http://fabtasticeats.com/2012/03/06/black-bean-burger-with-a-sriracha-sauce/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Black Bean Burger With Sriracha Sauce&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/recipes/black-bean-and-quinoa-burgers&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;meat-free burgers&lt;/a&gt; include red peppers, red onion, and green peppers, and stick together with panko breadcrumbs, egg, and black beans. The simple sauce is made up of non-fat plain yogurt, sriracha, and minced cilantro.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;18. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.inspiredtaste.net/6374/honey-sriracha-beef-skewers/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Honey Sriracha Beef Skewers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Marinate cubes of steak in a mixture of honey, soy sauce, and sriracha. Serve them skewered on giant Boston lettuce leaves with cucumber slices and sour cream (or use Greek yogurt as a healthier substitution).&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;19. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.inspiredtaste.net/15497/miso-mushroom-pasta-recipe/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Miso Mushroom Pasta&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This hearty meal is more pasta dish than soup, and combines a mushroom sauce with red miso paste, &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/greek-yogurt-snacks&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Greek yogurt&lt;/a&gt;, lime, sriracha, and broccoli florets. &quot;Healthify&quot; the recipe by using whole-wheat linguine.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;20. &lt;a href=&quot;http://putneyfarm.com/2012/05/15/seared-sea-scallops-with-sriracha-beurre-blanc/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Seared Scallops With Sriracha Beurre Blanc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;If you&rsquo;ve never heard of this fancy-sounding sauce, we&rsquo;ll clue you in. It&rsquo;s got minced shallots, rice wine vinegar, lemon juice, butter, sriracha, and fresh herbs. Plate the scallops with a sprinkle of &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/herb-guide/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;fresh herbs&lt;/a&gt;, a lemon wedge, and a drizzle of sauce.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;21. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.runningtothekitchen.com/2013/01/sriracha-lime-chicken-skillet/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha-Lime Chicken Skillet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This recipe doesn&rsquo;t require many ingredients or much effort (the oven does all the work). Toss chicken thighs in an oven-safe skillet with olive oil, lime juice, sriracha, and onion. Let the whole shabang hang out under a broiler toward the end of cooking to make it all nice and crispy.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;22. &lt;a href=&quot;http://inspiredrd.com/2012/08/chicken-coconut-curry-soup.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Chicken Curry Soup&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Coconut milk is a perfect way to mellow out the sriracha and curry paste in this flavorful soup. Once all the veggies are chopped and the chicken is diced, the &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/recipes/butternut-squash-chickpea-and-kale-curry&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;curry soup&lt;/a&gt; whips up in less than 15 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;23. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.olivesfordinner.com/2012/08/vegan-sausages-with-sriracha-and-five.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Vegan Sausages&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Vegan sausage&rdquo; may sound like an oxymoron, but this spiced up version uses refried beans and chickpea flour as a base. If liquid smoke isn&rsquo;t a pantry staple in your house, sub in Worcestershire sauce for equal flavor.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;24. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.weavethousandflavors.com/2012/03/sriracha-salmon-ceviche-towers-with-garden-guacamole-radish-sprouts-.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Salmon Ceviche Towers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These towers are &lt;em&gt;fancy&lt;/em&gt;. The stacks of deliciousness are formed by filling an empty can (with both ends removed) with layers of salmon, &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/best-guacamole-tricks&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;guacamole&lt;/a&gt;, and a sriracha-soy sauce. Radish and cucumber add a little crunch.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;25. &lt;a href=&quot;http://whiteonricecouple.com/recipes/baked-spaghetti-squash/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Baked Sriracha Spaghetti Squash With Turkey&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/spaghetti-squash-recipes&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spaghetti squash&lt;/a&gt;, the sneaky vegetable that pretends to be pasta, grows from a side dish into a main meal by adding in ground turkey. Onion, garlic, olive oil, fish sauce, and Sriracha season the squash.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;26. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.okiedokieartichokie.me/2012/04/salmon-and-cavatappi-pasta-salad-with-smoked-paprika-sriracha-sauce/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Salmon Sriracha Pasta Salad&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This recipe adds broiled, seasoned salmon to pasta (try whole-wheat for a healthier, more filling dish), fresh herbs, and greens. To up the health factor, use reduced-fat mayo and sub in plain Greek yogurt for the sour cream. This dish can be served warm or cold.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;27. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kalynskitchen.com/2011/08/recipe-for-grilled-sriracha-sesame.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Grilled Sriracha-Sesame Turkey Meatballs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Revamp meatballs with ground turkey, whole-wheat breadcrumbs, and the absence of fatty oils. Take meatballs out of the skillet and try cooking them on the grill for a smokier flavor profile.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Snacks&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;span   class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_full_width_inline_image&quot;   &gt;     &lt;img     src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/Sriracha%20Sesame%20Ginger%20Popcorn.jpg?itok=I0aYZuYS&quot;            alt=&quot;Sriracha Sesame Ginger Popcorn&quot;              class=&quot;media-element file-g-full-width-inline-image&quot;   /&gt;       &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;28. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bakeyourday.net/sriracha-sesame-ginger-popcorn/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Sesame Ginger Popcorn&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This isn&rsquo;t your average over-salted, over-fake-buttered movie theater snack. Give the popped kernels a good shake in a mixture of butter, olive oil, sriracha, sesame seeds, garlic, and ground ginger.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;29. &lt;a href=&quot;http://ohmyveggies.com/recipe-baked-sriracha-butternut-squash-fries/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Baked Sriracha Butternut Squash Fries&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Tell us one person who &lt;em&gt;doesn&rsquo;t&lt;/em&gt; like French fries. While some people may steer clear of the prized fry&rsquo;s lackluster nutritional value, these &ldquo;fries&rdquo; use butternut squash and an oven instead of potatoes and a deep fryer. Dip the sweet &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/recipes/baked-butternut-squash-fries&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;squash fries&lt;/a&gt; into a mixture of peanut oil and sriracha.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;30. &lt;a href=&quot;http://whiteonricecouple.com/recipes/spicy-white-bean-dip/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spicy White Bean Dip&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Hummus is cool and all, but when you need a change, try this hot soy sauce and sriracha-infused alternative. It&rsquo;s got a lot going on with lime juice, curry powder, and garlic and works well with whole-wheat pita or as a sandwich spread.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;31. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.anoregoncottage.com/2012/07/whole-wheat-sriracha-cheese-crackers/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Whole-Wheat Sriracha Cheese Crackers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These cheddary, spicy crackers aren&rsquo;t exactly as healthy as a handful of carrots. But if you&rsquo;re jonesing for a cheesy crunch (without all those hard-to-pronounce ingredients from processed versions), they&rsquo;re a great &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/45-healthy-foods-make-and-never-buy-again&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;homemade alternative&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;32. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.marthastewart.com/335370/sriracha-glazed-chicken&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha-Glazed Wings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Whisk up soy sauce, vinegar, sriracha, ginger, sesame oil, and a dash of sugar to coat chicken wings. Bake them in the oven until the sauce thickens up, and make sure to have a stack of napkins nearby. Feel free to use the glaze for spicy-sweet chicken breasts, too!&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;33. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.marthastewart.com/336841/shrimp-pot-stickers-with-sriracha-ginger&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Shrimp Pot Stickers with Sriracha-Ginger Dip&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These pot stickers are simple: Shrimp, carrot, and scallions get tucked inside wonton wrappers. The dipping sauce combines soy sauce, sriracha, sesame oil, &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/superfood-ginger&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;ginger,&lt;/a&gt; and a touch of sugar (as always, feel free to reduce the sugar). Serve as a party appetizer or use the glaze as a marinade for any protein.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;34. &lt;a href=&quot;http://mom.me/food/snacks/284-sriracha-cilantro-and-lime-roasted-chickpeas/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha, Cilantro, and Lime Roasted Chickpeas&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;We&rsquo;ve tackled crunchy, &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/recipe-spicy-roasted-chickpeas/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;roasted chickpeas&lt;/a&gt; before. This time, coat canned chickpeas (dried ones work too!) in a mixture of olive oil, sriracha, lime juice, sea salt, cilantro, and lime zest for a flavorful snack.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;35. &lt;a href=&quot;http://honestfare.com/simple-snack/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spicy Avocado Rice Cakes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Take a boring, dry rice cake to new levels with sriracha, avocado, and arugula. Choose a super-ripe avocado to make a spread that&rsquo;s more likely to stick to the crunchy cake.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;36. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.lifesambrosia.com/2009/11/sriracha-deviled-eggs-recipe.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Deviled Eggs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Deviled eggs can be the devil when they&rsquo;re loaded with mayo. Keep a this recipe healthy by using less &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/discover/sriracha-mayo&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;mayo&lt;/a&gt; (or choosing a reduced-fat variety), and add flavor with sriracha and garlic.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;37. &lt;a href=&quot;http://authenticsuburbangourmet.blogspot.com/2011/10/roasted-brussels-sprouts-with-sriracha.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Roasted Brussels With Sriracha Aioli&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Brussels sprouts get racy in this super easy recipe. Roast &lsquo;em up with a little olive oil, salt, and pepper, then dip them in a mixture of sriracha and reduced-fat mayo or plain Greek yogurt.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;38. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.munchinwithmunchkin.com/2012/06/12/taro-fries-with-sriracha-ketchup/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Taro Fries with Sriracha Ketchup&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Taro is kind of a funky root veggie, but makes for a great healthier version of &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/healthy-chip-alternatives/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;chips&lt;/a&gt; and fries with its nutty, slightly sweet flavor. Dip the fries in a mixture of ketchup, sriracha, and a touch of chili oil.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;39. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.busyinbrooklyn.com/spicy-roasted-edamame/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spicy Roasted Edamame&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This recipe has only five ingredients: Edamame, oil, soy sauce, sriracha, and wasabi powder. (Note: This recipe is almost guaranteed to open up your sinuses.) For a &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/high-protein-snacks-portable&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;protein-filled crunch&lt;/a&gt;, these spicy beans fit the bill.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;40. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kalynskitchen.com/2012/10/oven-fried-green-tomatoes.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Green Tomatoes With Sriracha Ranch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These &ldquo;fried&rdquo; green tomatoes are gluten-free (thanks to almond flour) and baked in an oven for a healthier take on the &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/healthy-recipe-alternatives-to-late-night-snacks&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;naughty pub fare&lt;/a&gt;. Dip each crispy tomato round into a mixture of ranch and sriracha, or skip the ranch and go straight to the Srirarcha for fewer calories.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Drinks&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;span   class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_full_width_inline_image&quot;   &gt;     &lt;img     src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/Strawberry%20Sriracha%20Margarita%202.jpg?itok=ZHdCoDXe&quot;            alt=&quot;Strawberry Sriracha Margarita&quot;              class=&quot;media-element file-g-full-width-inline-image&quot;   /&gt;       &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;41. &lt;a href=&quot;http://domesticfits.com/2012/07/30/strawberry-sriracha-margarita/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Strawberry Sriracha Margarita&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;This, we&rsquo;ve got to try. After blending up &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/healthier-margarita-recipes&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;margarita staples&lt;/a&gt;&mdash;strawberries, tequila, ice&mdash;bump up the spice level with a good helping of sriracha. (For a lesser-guilt beverage, feel free to cut back on the sugar.) Just get us a pool, some floaties, and we&rsquo;re in.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;42. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pepper.ph/sriracha-mango-cocktail-shots-not-for-sissies/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Mango Cocktail&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These shots are &ldquo;not for sissies.&rdquo; Each glass layers a mix of mango pur&eacute;e, whiskey, and lime with a base of sriracha. The little shooters start out sweet and then kick you right in the tush.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;43. &lt;a href=&quot;http://taste-for-adventure.tablespoon.com/2012/12/14/sriracha-honey-hot-toddy/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Hot Toddy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Normally, &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/drink-for-every-situation/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;hot toddies&lt;/a&gt; feature whiskey, lemon, and honey. This one draws from those basics, then heats things up with sriracha and ginger.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;44. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.birdandcleaver.com/2013/01/tgif-sriracha-wasabi-bloody-mary.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha and Wasabi Bloody Mary&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;A good bloody is known for its kick, but this one gets an extra &lt;em&gt;boom boom pow&lt;/em&gt; from the trio of wasabi, Worcestershire, and sriracha. The recipe makes enough for two, but we won&rsquo;t tell anyone if you chose not to share.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;45. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thekitchn.com/sriracha-in-my-beer-yes-please-the-cocky-rooster-175369&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Cocky Rooster&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Jazz up an ice-cold brew with sriracha. Add lime juice, sriracha, and jalape&ntilde;os to any lager-style beer (here&rsquo;s how to &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/healthier-beers/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;choose a healthier one&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;46. &lt;a href=&quot;http://cilantropist.blogspot.com/2011/03/spicy-ginger-citrus-cocktail-with-kale.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Ginger Citrus Cocktail&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Ginger and sriracha&mdash;often paired in food recipes&mdash;share the spotlight in this vodka-spiked cocktail. Serrano chilies make it even hotter.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Dessert&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;span   class=&quot;media media-element-container media-g_full_width_inline_image&quot;   &gt;     &lt;img     src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/Chocolate%20Sriracha%20Ice%20Cream%202.jpg?itok=aU-AB4vX&quot;            alt=&quot;Chocolate Sriracha Ice Cream&quot;              class=&quot;media-element file-g-full-width-inline-image&quot;   /&gt;       &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;47. &lt;a href=&quot;http://veganyackattack.com/2012/06/09/chocolate-sriracha-ice-cream/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Chocolate Sriracha Ice Cream&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Your mind may be blown, but sriracha in ice cream is a real thing. Coconut milk cools down the hot pepper flavor. Cocoa powder, ground cinnamon, and maple syrup also take a ride in the ice cream maker. Let's be honest: This dessert is no fruit kebab, but it&rsquo;s healthier than many store-bought frozen novelties.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;48. &lt;a href=&quot;http://acozykitchen.com/spicy-banana-fritters/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spicy Banana Fritters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Chunks of banana are literally painted with sriracha to make these fritters. They may not be &lt;em&gt;the&lt;/em&gt; healthiest choice, but at least we&rsquo;re getting some potassium as part of this sweet treat. Since frying isn't exactly a &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/healthy-cooking-methods/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;healthy cooking method&lt;/a&gt;, we recommend popping these tasty slices under the broiler instead.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;49. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.blogher.com/sriracha-peach-crisp&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Sriracha Peach Crisp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Add a scoop of low-fat vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt to this spicy peach-based dessert. Make a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.eatingwell.com/recipes/crumble_topping.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;healthier crumble topping&lt;/a&gt; with chopped nuts, oats, and whole-wheat flour.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h4&gt;50. &lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.thesrirachacookbook.com/post/25518541586/sriracha-ice-cream-milkshake-go-burger&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spicy Strawberry Milkshake&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;  &lt;p&gt;For a slightly healthier take on this scrumptious recipe, combine nonfat or low fat strawberry frozen yogurt, skip the graham cracker crumbs, and add sriracha and whipped cream for a spicy but cold, semi-&ldquo;healthy&rdquo; dessert.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Originally posted February 2013. Updated April 2015.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ",
